    • Method Detail

      • checkingSpawnEvent

        public void checkingSpawnEvent(org.spongepowered.api.event.entity.SpawnEntityEvent event)
        Runs when an entity spawns, and decides whether a spawn egg should replace the entity or not.

        This runs through several checks:

        1. The plugin is enabled
        2. The entity is not summoned by the plugin
        3. The entity is summoned from a breeding event
        4. The entity is the proper entity type as determined by EntitiesID.ALL_ENTITIES
        5. The entity passes the prng chosen by the JVM
        Parameters:
        event - runs when any entity spawns in the world

      • setData

        public void setData(BreedingData data)
        Sets the data of the breeding manager to whatever the inputted data is.

        Any incorrect values will be fixed here, as said by BreedingData.setGlobalChance(int), BreedingData.setIndividualMobChance(int[]), and BreedingData.setDebugLevel(int). Config data will outputted according to BreedingData.setDebugLevel(int).

        Parameters:
        data - the inputted data
